public void testLoadISO88591Encoding() throws IOException {
    ExtendedProperties ep = new ExtendedProperties();
    // Create a temporary file with ISO-8859-1 encoded content
    File tempFile = File.createTempFile("test", ".properties");
    tempFile.deleteOnExit();
    // Write property with non-ASCII character é (ISO-8859-1 code 0xE9)
    try (FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(tempFile);
         OutputStreamWriter osw = new OutputStreamWriter(fos, "ISO-8859-1")) {
        osw.write("key=é");
    }
    // Load with null encoding (should fallback to ISO-8859-1)
    try (FileInputStream fis = new FileInputStream(tempFile)) {
        ep.load(fis, null);
    }
    assertEquals("é", ep.getProperty("key"));
}

But note: The load method we are testing is the two-argument one. This should work.

